Probability generating function
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The probability generating function is a convenient tool which simplifies
 calculations involving nonnegative, integer valued random variables.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
The probability generating function of a nonnegative integer valued random
 variable 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
G_{X}(z)=\sum_{i=0}^{\infty}p_{i}z^{i}
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $G_{X}(z)$
\end_inset

 is also known as the 
\begin_inset Formula $z-$
\end_inset

transform of 
\begin_inset Formula $X$
\end_inset

 and converges for all 
\begin_inset Formula $z\in\mathbb{C}$
\end_inset

 with 
\begin_inset Formula $\mid z\mid<1$
\end_inset

.
 By definition of 
\begin_inset Formula $G_{X}$
\end_inset

 we have that 
\begin_inset Formula $G_{X}(1)=1$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

